BEGIN_TEXT
Sketch the graph of the function \(f\) to determine the type of discontinuity at each \(x\)-value.
\[
f(x) = \begin{cases}
x^2+2, &\text{ if } x < -3     \\
-5, &\text{ if } x = -3       \\
$a x+ 2, &\text{ if } -3 < x \le 0 \\
\displaystyle \frac{-$b x}{(x-3)^2}, &\text{ if } 0 < x < 3 \\
\displaystyle \frac{1}{x^2+1}, &\text{ if } 3 \le x \\
\end{cases}
\]
$PAR
